Please follow these project-specific guidelines:

1. Package Management:
- Use pnpm exclusively for package management
- Install dependencies with: pnpm install
- Add new dependencies with: pnpm add [package-name]
- Add dev dependencies with: pnpm add -D [package-name]

2. Code Style:
- Write all new files in TypeScript
- Follow the ESLint configuration
- Follow existing code structure and naming conventions

3. Project Structure:
- Place React components in src/components/
- Custom React hooks go in src/hooks/
- State management code belongs in src/stores/
- TypeScript types should be in src/types/
- Utility functions go in src/utils/

4. Git Commits:
- Use Conventional Commits format (https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/)
- Write commit messages in present tense
- Use lowercase letters throughout commit messages

5. Testing Requirements:
- Write tests for new features
- Run tests before submitting PR using: pnpm test
- Ensure all tests pass

6. Pull Request Process:
- Create a feature branch
- Make your changes
- Run tests and linting
- Submit PR with clear description
- Address review comments

Please ensure all code changes adhere to these guidelines. 